            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> File outline based on treesitter. This is mostly useful for not sending more data than needed to LLMs, and also for filtering data using keyword search which is much more reliable than full text search\n\nWhat about exposing some internal functions that power `vim.lsp.buf.document_symbol()` and `vim.lsp.buf.workspace_symbol()` so we can get this for free? (with the only difference is that this file outline feature would be LSP-based instead of Treesitter-based)",
            "created_at": "2025-05-31T10:47:41Z",
