        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> What the motivation for doing something so new and underdeveloped directly in core?\n\nThe core parts of this feature are generally useful. The path to getting this feature will involve enhancements to the state/context features (`nvim_get_context()`, shada, etc), which themselves will be useful to the \"third party plugins\".\n\nThe final \"context digest\" feature is a very thin layer on top of that. We can debate whether we want that, depending on how it turns out. Nevertheless, such a feature is low-risk because AI inputs do not have rigorous requirements, so we can easily change its output as needed.\n\n> What about exposing some internal functions that power vim.lsp.buf.document_symbol() and vim.lsp.buf.workspace_symbol() so we can get this for free?\n\nObviously the \"digest\" will leverage lsp, treesitter, and any kind of info (state) that we think of.",
