        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think this issue is quite outdated now. I don't know any popular editor MCP that will dump all editor states, directory structures, workspace symbols in a single prompt. Instead I tend to see agents query for what they want via MCP tools instead (I rarely see any MCP resources being implemented.)\n\nAnd which and how MCP tools should be implemented is also very debatable (see JetBrain MCP vs Serena, they both provide IDE related tools, but they have very different tools list and design).",
            "created_at": "2026-02-23T13:06:36Z",
