        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Instead I tend to see agents query for what they want via MCP tools\n\nTrue. Though it's easy to exceed the context window with frivolous MCP responses. And models can use up a lot of tokens (and time) trying to figure out what they actually want.\n\nSo it may still be worth leveraging [Nvim's own context/shada state](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32949#issuecomment-2927762246) to produce an \"optimal\" outline. (That is a similar principle used by [beads](https://github.com/steveyegge/beads), which btw, was later used in openclaw...)\n\nBut to avoid attracting extra discussion here until Nvim's core \"introspection\" features are mature, we can close this for now.",
